  "prompt": "What hotel in Patna would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "Finding a hotel in Patna that is safe and welcoming for unmarried couples can be challenging due to societal norms and occasional interference from authorities. However, some hotels are more accommodating and discreet. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Hotel Maurya Patna**  \n   A well-known and reputable hotel, Hotel Maurya is generally safe and professional in its approach. It\u2019s a high-end option that is unlikely to cause unnecessary trouble for unmarried couples.\n\n2. **Lemon Tree Premier, Patna**  \n   This is a modern hotel with a good reputation for hospitality. They tend to be more open-minded and professional, making it a safer choice.\n\n3. **The Panache**  \n   A mid-range hotel that is known for being couple-friendly and discreet. It\u2019s a good option for those looking for a comfortable stay without unnecessary scrutiny.\n\n4. **Treebo Trend Kapil Dev**  \n   Part of a trusted budget hotel chain, Treebo hotels are generally couple-friendly and maintain a professional environment.\n\n5. **Oyo Townhouse**  \n   Oyo properties are often a safe bet for unmarried couples, as they follow a standardized approach and are less likely to cause issues.\n\n### Tips for a Safe Stay:\n- **Book in Advance:** Always book online and check reviews to ensure the hotel is couple-friendly.\n- **Carry Valid IDs:** Both partners should carry valid government-issued IDs for check-in.\n- **Confirm Policies:** Call the hotel beforehand to confirm their policies for unmarried couples.\n- **Be Discreet:** Avoid drawing unnecessary attention during your stay.\n\nWhile these hotels are generally safe, it\u2019s always a good idea to stay informed and cautious, as local attitudes and enforcement can vary.",
